<br>
The jade mace is technically better in the main hand then a Lamentation.. but to be honest critter to critter there is no real difference.  I won't go into the details but for that small a margin in delay a fight would have to last close to forever to make even the smallest of difference.  The stats on the Lamentation and low weight make it much more useful in my opinion.  For your off hand ratio is the overiding issue since damage bonus is not applied.  But many of the formula's get this wrong imo.  It really depends on where the haste cap really is.  If you have the gear and buffs to get to the haste cap from a 24 delay weapon then essentially the crystalline short sword will rock.  Since both weapons will be of about the same delay then a 9dmg cap delay weapon is inferior to a 12dmg cap delay weapon.  The argument then is the xtra damage you get from the off hand sword worth it?  I have a 9dmg 20dly in my off hand but would use the 12/24 if I did not get 10ac out of the swordbreaker.  <br>
<br>
Does the offhand swing enough to make up for the incredible stats on the lamentation?  Are both swords essentially the same delay due to the haste cap?  Where is the point where there is enough stats to justify a drop in dmg output?  These are all questions you need to ask yourself.<br>
<br>
Since the piercing skill caps lower then the other weapons skills the trident is not worth it at all.  In addition since there will be only a small trade off in damage potential against a lamentation and the very benifitial stats of the lamentation this one is a easy call.  Trade away the Jarsath for something you will use.. even a non-weapon or even cash.<br>
<br>
Your mileage of course may vary.. get a few more opinions as well.  Never hurts.. but if anyone tells you to keep the Jarsath over the other options you have I probably would not take anything they say too seriously.<br>
